craftinginfo-toolmaking-text:
toolmaking

Neolithic Tool Making 101. Only here on The Neolithic Mod.

In the neolithic mod, hafted flint or stone (e.g. granite) tools are fully created outside your crafting grid. You will create them step by step on a workspace block in front of you. You will need a flint tool/weapon head, a shaft, and binding material to attach the tool or weapon head to the shaft. The first step is to create the tool head using the knapping interface. If you wish to make a tool or weapon using a head that you prepared ahead of time, or you found by panning, Shift (Sneak) + Right click will allow you to place the flint head and create a workspace. Once the head is made or placed, it will remain on the block where you knapped or placed it, which will become your workspace. Next, you will need to add a shaft, either debarked very thin branch or large bone. Right click the workspace to add the shaft to your knapped flint or stone head. The last step is to secure the shaft to the tool/weapon head using sisal twine, sinew or leather strips. Right click the workspace to add the binding and complete your tool. The completed tool will stay on the workspace block until you Left click (break) and pick it up.

Congratulations! You are now a master Tool Maker \o/
item-arrow-fire*: Fire Arrow crafted from any any arrow, fat and a torch
itemdesc-arrow-fire*: Adds +2 damage. Future recipe should include adding linen or other fiber. Could include pitch if liquids like that are added.
item-arrow-poison*: Poisoned Arrow crafted from any arrow and mushroom
itemdesc-arrow-poison*: Adds +2 damage. Future recipe should include cooking with a herb to get poison.
itemdesc-bow-simple: Flimsy stick with some weak string.  Make a strong bowstring using animal sinew and carve a better limb.
itemdesc-bow-carved: A little better than a flimsy stick.  Made by combining a carved limb with a bowstring. Replace bowstring before it breaks and destroys the bow.
itemdesc-bow-composite: A decent bow made by gluing layers of horn and sinew onto a carved bow limb. Replace bowstring before it breaks and destroys the bow.
itemdesc-bow-recurve: Advanced bow made by adding hide and more horn and sinew to composite limb. Replace bowstring before it breaks and destroys the bow.
itemdesc-bamboostakes-brown: Arrange in the grid 2 x 2 to make Brown Bamboo Planks
itemdesc-bamboostakes-green: Arrange in the grid 2 x 2 to make Green Bamboo Planks
blockdesc-mortar-*: In the crafting grid with a Pestle to make the Mortar and Pestle
blockdesc-pestle-*: In crafting grid with a Mortar to make the Mortar and Pestle
itemdesc-reeds: Can be used for all recipes that require cattails
itemdesc-flake-*: Flakes are used to make the Primitive Sword
blockdesc-bowl-*-sinewfibers: Cook in a firepit to make a bowl of glue.
